<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static void insertDeleteInstructions (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &#42; MBB, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &amp; MI, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &#42; &gt; &amp; InsInstrs, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &#42; &gt; &amp; DelInstrs, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinetracemetrics/ensemble">MachineTraceMetrics::Ensemble</a> &#42; TraceEnsemble, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sparseset">SparseSet</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/liveregunit">LiveRegUnit</a> &gt; &amp; RegUnits, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetinstrinfo">TargetInstrInfo</a> &#42; TII, unsigned Pattern, bool IncrementalUpdate)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Inserts InsInstrs and deletes DelInstrs.

Incrementally updates instruction depths if requested.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="MBB">basic block to insert instructions in</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="MI">current machine instruction</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="InsInstrs">new instructions to insert in <code>MBB</code></ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="DelInstrs">instruction to delete from <code>MBB</code></ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="TraceEnsemble">is a pointer to the machine trace information</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="RegUnits">set of live registers, needed to compute instruction depths</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="TII">is target instruction info, used to call target hook</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="<a href=&quot;/docs/api/classes/llvm/pattern&quot;>Pattern</a>">is used to call target hook finalizeInsInstrs</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="IncrementalUpdate">if true, compute instruction depths incrementally, otherwise invalidate the trace</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// FIXME: for now, we don&#39;t do any check for the register pressure patterns.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;unsigned, 16&gt;</a> Patterns;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The motivating example is:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//     MUL  Other        MUL&#95;op1 MUL&#95;op2  Other</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      \\    /               \\      |    /</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      ADD/SUB      =&gt;        MADD/MSUB</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      (=Root)                (=NewRoot)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The DAGCombine code always replaced MUL + ADD/SUB by MADD. While this is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// usually beneficial for code size it unfortunately can hurt performance</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// when the ADD is on the critical path, but the MUL is not. With the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// substitution the MUL becomes part of the critical path (in form of the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// MADD) and can lengthen it on architectures where the MADD latency is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// longer than the ADD latency.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For each instruction we check if it can be the root of a combiner</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// pattern. Then for each pattern the new code sequence in form of MI is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// generated and evaluated. When the efficiency criteria (don&#39;t lengthen</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// critical path, don&#39;t use more resources) is met the new sequence gets</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// hooked up into the basic block before the old sequence is removed.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The algorithm does not try to evaluate all patterns and pick the best.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This is only an artificial restriction though. In practice there is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// mostly one pattern, and getMachineCombinerPatterns() can order patterns</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// based on an internal cost heuristic. If</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// machine-combiner-verify-pattern-order is enabled, all patterns are</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// checked to ensure later patterns do not provide better latency savings.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (!<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/hexagon/hexagoncopytocombine-cpp/#a1d40004718218dbdf06b496766299101">TII</a>-&gt;getMachineCombinerPatterns(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/lib/codegen/globalisel/irtranslator-cpp/#abe44dfdea65b4f7e11e0a608ab708b76">MI</a>, Patterns, DoRegPressureReduce))</Highlight></CodeLine>
